Description: Return from the flight into Egypt; a procession led by two cherubs sprinkling flower petals on the ground followed by angels playing instruments; two putti hold a basket of hay between them and feed the donkey carrying the Virgin and child; at the rear Joseph holds a saw over his shoulder; beyond is a ruined building; putti frolic in a palm tree; after Karel van Mander Engraving
Producer name: Print made by: Jacques de Gheyn II
Curator's comments: The impression is cut to the design.
Bibliographic references: New Hollstein (Dutch & Flemish) / The New Hollstein: Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts 1450-1700 (33.I) (The De Gheyn family)
Acquisition name: Purchased through: H G Gutekunst (sale Stuttgart 22-31.v.1871/1759)
